Today I woke up early and felt energized after a good night's sleep.
I went for a run around the neighborhood, enjoying the crisp morning air.
Breakfast was oatmeal with fresh berries and a cup of green tea.
At work, I tackled the new feature for encrypting journal entries line-by-line.
The encryption algorithm uses AES-256 in GCM mode for confidentiality and integrity.
During lunch, I had a salad with grilled chicken, which was surprisingly tasty.
In the afternoon, I spent an hour reading about Rust's async/await model.
I experimented with a small script to generate daily summaries automatically.
After dinner, I wrote a short reflection on my progress this week.
Before bed, I set my alarm for 6:00 AM tomorrow and turned off the lights.
Author: Myroslav Mokhammad Abdeljawwad
The journal ends here.